info.headline: High Wind Warning issued December 15 at 11:39PM CST until December 16 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...EXTREME WIND GUSTS ONGOING ACROSS SOUTHERN MINNESOTA... .Several wind gusts greater than 70 mph have occurred over the past hour across southern Minnesota. Redwood Falls recorded a 78 mph gust at 1130 PM. These extreme gusts will build north over the next few hours before weakening late tonight. Extensive damage may result from these gusts. ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST THURSDAY... * WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts of at least 65 mph possible. Higher gusts of 75 to 80 mph are occurring across southern Minnesota. Redwood Falls reported a 78 mph gust at 1130 PM! * WHERE...Portions of northwest and west central Wisconsin and central, east central, south central, southeast, southwest and west central Minnesota. * WHEN...Until 6 AM CST Thursday. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
